4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.1986521a-0fc9-4962-a47c-4afe989cf2f4.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.19d46f50-c3a4-4bcf-bd41-cd846c1822d3.prompt=Enter a value for value2 4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.1b306d97-fedc-4e13-bf47-7b67bf27b464.description=
Runs a SQL query against an Oracle database, using the information available in the tnsnames.ora file.  
The first row is returned on the first run of the operation.
Subsequent calls with the same information will return the other rows.

Inputs\:
TNSPath - The path to the parent folder of the TNS file which contains the DB connecting info(the name of the DB server, the port used for connecting to the DB server, the database name).
TNSEntry - The entry name from the tnsnames.ora file which contains the connecting information.
Username - The username used for connecting to the database.
Password - The password used for connecting to the database.
Command - The command to execute.
Delimiter - Delimiter to use between columns in returnResult.
Key - Key to help keep multiple query results distinct.

Responses\:
more items - More rows are available for retrieval.
no more items - No more rows are available.
failure - There was an error executing the command.

Extra Results\:
columnNames - The names of all the columns returned, separated by Delimiter.
rowsLeft - The number of rows remaining that match the query.

NOTE\: 
This op supports only Oracle. The tnsnames.ora file should be correctly configured on the RAS machine.

ORACLE NOTE\:
Only the "SELECT" statement can be executed using this operation. For statements that modify the database, use "TNS Names SQL Command".
4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.3b38d396-2ca1-4963-a5e9-e2ad3bc12e6e.description=
This is an operation that does nothing. It can be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.
4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.8a7eeab9-098c-4ada-b3f8-f0ad22ab38e7.description=
Resolves any flow variables in a String. This is useful if you have an input to a flow that references undefined flow variables, and define them later. Pass in the flow variable key name of the string that contains unresolved flow variables.

Inputs\:
keyName - The name of the flow variable that should have its value reresolved.
eraseUnresolved - A boolean value. If true, any unresolved flow variable references will be replaced by nothing (IE ${variable} disappears).

Responses\:
success - One or more flow variables were replaced, or could not be resolved and were erased from the string.
failure - No flow variables were referenced in the string.

Returns\:
The resulting string having had flow variable references replaced with the resolved values.
4dbd66b1-7be7-48bb-ab51-449e4fd8239d.a748cb18-512d-420d-9778-859286335d78.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal
